title: Spotlight Pt. 26.2*
body:
You’ve been discharged for a couple hours now, the boys had to go to BigHit soon after dropping you off but you easily convinced them you’d be fine while they’re gone. They insisted you stay with them while you heal even though they leave for tour in a couple months. At this rate they’d probably end up taking you with them considering how worried they’ve been about you in the past 24 hours. At least one of them has been checking on you every 20-30 minutes and you idly wonder how they get any work done texting you all day.

Summary: when shit hit the fan y/n used it as the push she needed to finally leave her home and take a leap of faith landing her in one of the world’s busiest cities. Seoul, South Korea. Running from more than a couple dark secrets of her past y/n tries to move forward with her new life and not so lowkey friends she met over the past couple years, but you can’t outrun your past now, can you?

title: Spotlight Pt. 27*
body:
One Month Later

“Y/n are you ready to go?” Jungkook asks coming in to Yoongi and Jin’s room where you had been staying.

The boys really are dragging you on tour with them. You were beyond shocked when the boys told you they were dragging you with them on tour but you couldn’t hide your excitement knowing you won’t have to spend the next four months away from your best friends, and boyfriend.

“Just about.” You say attempting to move around on your own. Yoongi comes in shortly after and lifts you up.

“We’re running late princess. Jungkook grab her suitcase and crutches.” He says carrying you easily out of the room and out to the car where the others are already waiting. He sits you inside and slides in next to you as Jungkook puts your bag in the trunk and gets in the car. The eight of you make your way to the airport chatting back and forth as the boys try to prepare you for the chaos that will be the next four months. You listen attentively to everything they tell you silently worrying you’ll get in the way with your inability to walk properly. You’ve gotten better with the crutches but with how fast paced their lives are going to be you doubt you’ll be able to keep up. When you arrive at the airport there are at least a thousand fans standing around screaming and taking pictures of the boys. Their mangers and staff rush the boys through the crowds to get to your flight but Yoongi keeps pace with you, not leaving your side for even a moment. He’s been like that with you all month, whenever he’s not monumentally busy he’s babying you, following you everywhere and helping with things you can do on your own. You appreciate the help though since it can be frustrating trying to maneuver with the crutches. Once you’re all on the plane the boys slowly start dozing off since the flight is nearly 12 hours long. It takes you a little longer to fall asleep, your mind buzzing with the excitement of returning to the states for the first time in two years. And you were doing it with the people you consider family, and the love your life. You lay your head on Yoongi’s shoulder and finally manage to fall asleep happily cuddled into his side. To get to this point almost makes all the drama recently worth it.

Summary: when shit hit the fan y/n used it as the push she needed to finally leave her home and take a leap of faith landing her in one of the world’s busiest cities. Seoul, South Korea. Running from more than a couple dark secrets of her past y/n tries to move forward with her new life and not so lowkey friends she met over the past couple years, but you can’t outrun your past now, can you?

Spotlight Pt. 27/27

So this is THE END you guys. Was the ending shit? I wasn’t sure if I closed up all the plot points, but it’s over now so hopefully you liked the journey :)

I didn’t know this would be the last part until literally right now. As I’m writing this little note thanking you all for reading my story.

This is my first attempt at a social media au so I hope I did alright

I’m pretty proud of it so if you hate it screw you I don’t care XD
